spider man: far from home reference
body:
Spider-Kiss

Lil ficlet I made of ITSV’s Miles and Gwen hanging out after a hard day of fighting crime❤️🕸💗

They swayed on their web ropes in a narrow, secluded alley, hanging upside down. Gwen Stacy’s web was attached to a lamppost, while Miles Morales, inches across from her, had attached his to the roof top of a small building. The place was filled with graffiti, none of which were the works of Miles, but he did appreciate the artistry of the spray painted insignias. The two young heroes just hung there, observing each other and relaxing after a hard days’ work.

“Have I ever told you you’re beautiful?”, Miles asked smiling. Gwen smirked, ”I don’t think so”, she said. “You want to hear it?”, Miles teased. “Sure, whatever”, Gwen teased back. Miles rolled his shoulders back and grinned. “Well, you’re beautiful”, he told her. Gwen narrowed her eyes, “so, therefore, I have worth?”, “uhhh”, Miles was taken aback by her response. Her eyes then lit up again and she let out a sparkling laugh, “I’m just kidding. I think you’re beautiful, too”. Miles chuckled confusedly, “oh…kay..?” I feel like this has already been done somewhere else, Miles thought to himself. He then gazed at the girl in front of him again. “So uh…are we, like, still friends, or can I start calling you something else-“, Miles gasped as Gwen leaned forward and caught his lips in her own and the back of his head in her hand.

For a while Miles didn’t do anything but freeze in place bug-eyed, but he eventually let his eyes flutter partially closed and grabbed the hair on her head that he loved so much to lean into the kiss. Her lips tasted like cake batter chapstick. Who knew that his first kiss would be the famous spider-kiss that all spider-men and women were known to have at least once in their life?

Gwen pulled back after a while and smiled, “does that answer your question?”, she asked. “Yeah”, Miles grinned dreamily, “that did feel kinda weird though with all the blood rushing to our heads”. Gwen shrugged,”it could just be that you’re blushing”. “Nah, I’m pretty sure it’s mostly because we’re upside down. Are you blushing, Gwen?”, Miles teased. Gwen crosses her arms and smirked, “I don’t have to tell you anything, Morales”. Miles laughed, “that’s my girl! You never change, Gwen”.

“Oh, and I’m not your girl”, Gwen added smugly. Miles feigned sadness, “but why?” “Because you’re my little pushover who listens to and obeys everything I say”, Gwen teased smugly. “Whaaat? I am not a pushover!”, Miles exclaimed. “Yes you are”, “no I’m not”, “yeah you are”, “nuh-uh”, “uh-huh”, “prove it”, “fine”.

Gwen pulled Miles’ face back to hers and kissed him once more, and he followed to return the kiss. “See, you always reciprocate only after I initiate, which you never do”, Gwen stated matter-of-factly. Miles rolled his eyes and huffed, “we’ve only kissed two times! And I can initiate a kiss!” “Sure you can”, Gwen dared. Miles swung a bit forward on his web to crash his lips into hers in a deep kiss, one hand going into her sunflower hair to massage it. He could’ve sworn he heard Gwen gasp a little but after they broke the kiss she was still looking just as smug. “You only initiated that after I mentioned it, though”, Gwen pointed out. “Yeah but you liked it, Gwen Stacy”, Miles retorted with a goofy grin on his face.

“Shut up, Miles”, Gwen giggled.

Feedback is appreciated!
